```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    if isnan(dt.t) || isnull(dt.t)
        throw(ArgumentError("Cannot bump a DateTime with an NaN or null timestamp"))
    end
    return DateTime(dt.year, dt.month, dt.day, dt.hour + bump, dt.minute, dt.second, dt.millisecond, tz = dt.tz)
end
```

This function checks if the timestamp of the `DateTime` object is `NaN` or `null`, and throws an error if so. It then adds the specified number of hours to the hour component of the `DateTime` and returns the updated `DateTime` object. The default value for `bump` is set to 3 hours.
